@Allisterm The best things about working from home are sleeping in, being able to do chores during break, seeing colleagues in a more relaxed light... that we're allowed to show our more human selves.

@Allisterm The biggest thing that made the situation easier has been working in a team that is full of people who genuinely care about each other and the work.

@Allisterm Having said that, institutions face certain pressures to deliver, so the hardest part about the pandemic is planning ahead, adjusting to unpredictable changes and making decisions that feel safe, thoughtful and timely...
